<#
.SYNOPSIS
    This PowerShell script controls who is explicitly blocked from connecting over the network (SMB, RPC, remote access paths, etc.) 
This ensures that:
 Highly privileged accounts (like Domain Admins) are blocked from network logon to workstations
 Local accounts are blocked where required (on domain-joined systems)
 Unauthenticated or anonymous access is denied
    
